            <li><a href="#software12">Can I change the size of my photo book while I’m halfway designing
                it?</a></li>
            <li><a href="#software13">How do I add more pages to my photo book?</a></li>
            <li><a href="#software14">Can I insert a page in between two pages I’ve previously created?</a></li>
            <li><a href="#software15">Will the photos I’ve uploaded onto photobook editor disappear
                when I close the program?</a></li>
            <li><a href="#software16">Do I have to remain connected to the Internet to design my
                photo book?</a></li>
        </ol>
        <p>
            <strong>Answers:</strong></p>
        <ol>
            <ol>
                <li><strong><a id="software01" name="software01"></a>I am not familiar with designing
                    work, is it difficult for me to work with your software?</strong><br />
                    Our software is designed to be used by everybody, no prior knowledge in design software
                    is required.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#softwaretop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="software02" name="software02"></a>Where do I select the type of paper
                    &amp; colour my photo book?</strong><br />
                    As you proceed with ordering your photo book, these options are available for your
                    selection on the payment page.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#softwaretop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="software03" name="software03"></a>What kind of picture formats can
                    i use for my photo book?</strong></li>
            </ol>
        </ol>
        <blockquote>
            <ul>
                <li>RGB, CMYK or Grayscale JPEG</li>
                <li>RGB, CMYK or Grayscale TIFF</li>
                <li>PNG images</li>
            </ul>
        </blockquote>
        <blockquote>
            <p>
                <a href="#softwaretop">
                    <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                        border="0" />
                    Back to top</a></p>
        </blockquote>
        <ol>
            <ol>
                <li><strong><a id="software04" name="software04"></a>How do i upload my photos to the
                    software?</strong><br />
                    Look for the Add Images icon + at the bottom left panel. Once you click on it, a
                    window will pop-up, prompting you to select the folder where your photos are stored.
                    Select the folder, then your choice of photos and click ‘OK’. You can also click
                    on the Select All button at the top left corner if you would like all the photos
                    to be uploaded.Or if you have a full folder of pictures which you would like to
                    upload, then click on the Add Folder with Images. All your photos are now ready
                    to be placed in to your photo book.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#softwaretop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="software05" name="software05"></a>How do I put my photos on the page?</strong><br />
                    Your photos will first appear as thumbnails at the bottom panel on Photo Book Editor.
                    To place them in your photo book, just drag and drop them on to your desired page
                    and position.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#softwaretop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="software06" name="software06"></a>What is the best resolution for
                    photos in my photo book?</strong><br />
                    photobookmart recommends using resolution of 240dpi and above. If your photos are
                    of a lower resolution, they may appear blurred or pixelated in the finished product.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#softwaretop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="software07" name="software07"></a>How do I know if my photos are
                    of the minimum required resolution?</strong><br />
                    In your photo folder, right-click on the selected image, choose Properties &gt;
                    Details. Look for the ‘Horizontal Resolution’ and ‘Vertical Resolution’. You can
                    then see if your photo meets the minimum requirement of 240dpi.You will then see
                    an additional bar just above your photo book thumbnails. If you mouse over each
                    square shown, you will be able to see what errors exist on every page – including
                    low resolution photos.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#softwaretop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="software08" name="software08"></a>What if the resolution of my photos
                    is below the minimum requirement?</strong><br />
                    Unless you are well-versed with photo enhancing software such as Photoshop, we recommend
                    for you to retake the photo or simply use another alternative.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#softwaretop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="software09" name="software09"></a>I can’t upload my photos on to
                    the software. What should I do?</strong><br />
                    Check if your images match the following requirements.</li>
            </ol>
        </ol>
        <blockquote>
            <ul>
                <li>JPEG, TIFF or PNG formats. PNGs should be 8-bit and non-interlaced</li>
                <li>sRGB colour (no CMYK nor Grayscale nor Adobe 1998 RGB)</li>
                <li>If you’re using iPhoto, ensure that your photo library has its default name and
                    is saved in its default location</li>
                <li>150 to 300 dpi in resolution</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                P/s: You can check the above details by right clicking on the selected image and
                then selecting Properties.<br />
                If you’re still facing problems, do get in touch with our Customer Service Department.</p>
        </blockquote>
        <blockquote>
            <p>
                <a href="#softwaretop">
                    <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                        border="0" />
                    Back to top</a></p>
        </blockquote>
        <ol>
            <ol>
                <li><strong><a id="software10" name="software10"></a>Does Photo Book Editor come with
                    image-enhancing features?</strong><br />
                    You can perform basic enhancements on your photos with Photo Book Editor such as
                    zooming in and out on a particular portion, moving away unattractive portions or
                    backgrounds, improving picture brightness and vibrance, adding a sepia or black
                    and white effect on them and more.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#softwaretop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="software11" name="software11"></a>If I delete or alter my photos
                    on photobook editor, will it affect the original photo?</strong><br />
                    No. They will only appear deleted, altered or enhanced on the software, not on the
                    original file.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#softwaretop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="software12" name="software12"></a>Can I change the size of my photo
                    book while I’m halfway designing it?</strong><br />
                    Unfortunately, you can’t. If you wish to have another size, you will need to start
                    another new project.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#softwaretop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="software13" name="software13"></a>How do I add more pages to my photo
                    book?</strong><br />
                    Click on Insert &gt; Append New Page. The new pages will be added from the last
                    page onwards. You can also find this command when you right-click on the page.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#softwaretop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="software14" name="software14"></a>Can I insert a page in between
                    two pages I’ve previously created?</strong><br />
                    Not a problem! Just click on Insert &gt; Insert New Page.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#softwaretop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="software16" name="software15"></a>Will the photos I’ve uploaded onto
                    photobook editor disappear when I close the program?</strong><br />
                    As long as you save your project before closing, no.</li>
            </ol>
        </ol>
        <blockquote>
            <p>
                <a href="#softwaretop">
                    <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                        border="0" />
                    Back to top</a></p>
        </blockquote>
        <ol>
            <li><strong><a id="software17" name="software16"></a>Do I have to remain connected to
                the Internet to design my photo book?</strong><br />
                You don’t have to be connected to the Internet unless you want to place your order
                or refer to the photobookmart website.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
