            <li><a href="#design27">Can I save my photo book and finish designing it later?</a></li>
        </ol>
        <p>
            <strong>Answers:</strong></p>
        <ol>
            <ol>
                <li><strong><a id="design01" name="design01"></a>Do you provide services like helping
                    customers to make amendments to their files?</strong><br />
                    Because we receive many files every day, we are unable to help customers to make
                    amendments to the files submitted. It is your responsibility to ensure the files
                    are 100% good for printing before placing your orders.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#designtop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="design02" name="design02"></a>Can I choose the colour of my photo
                    book cover too?</strong><br />
                    Definitely! Click here to see what colours can be incorporated into your photo book
                    cover.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#designtop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="design03" name="design03"></a>What is considered one page? A spread
                    of both sides or just one side?</strong><br />
                    The pagination of your photo book is similar to an ordinary book. Each page that
                    you flip is considered one page.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#designtop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="design04" name="design04"></a>How do I put my photos on the page?</strong><br />
                    Your photos will first appear as thumbnails at the bottom panel on Photo Book Editor.
                    To place them in your photo book, just drag and drop them on to your desired page
                    and position.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#designtop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="design05" name="design05"></a>How many photos can I put inside my
                    book?</strong><br />
                    As long as it is within the maximum page count and file size, you can place as many
                    photos as you like.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#designtop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="design06" name="design06"></a>How do I change the size of a photo
                    I’ve placed on a page?</strong><br />
                    Select the photo you wish to resize and drag any of its corners in or out accordingly
                    to reduce or increase the photo.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#designtop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="design07" name="design07"></a>How do I zoom in and out on a particular
                    portion of my photo?</strong><br />
                    Simply click on the Zoom In (Insert Magnifying tool with plus sign) or Zoom Out
                    (insert magnifying glass with minus sign) icons to adjust accordingly.</p>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            <a href="#designtop">
                                <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                    border="0" />
                                Back to top</a></p>
                    </blockquote>
                </li>
                <li><strong><a id="design08" name="design08"></a>How do I move unattractive portions
                    or backgrounds on my photo away?</strong></li>
            </ol>
        </ol>
        <blockquote>
            <ul>
                <li>Select your picture</li>
                <li>You will see four directional arrows in the middle. Depending on which part of the
                    photo you’d like to see more (or less of), drag your mouse over the left, right,
                    up or down arrows respectively.<a href="#designtop"><img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif"
                        width="11" height="10" border="0" />
                        Back to top</a></li>
            </ul>
        </blockquote>
        <ol>
            <li><strong><a id="design09" name="design09"></a>How do I improve picture brightness
                and vibrance?</strong><br />
                You can either click on the Perfectly Clear Image icon at the editing taskbar or
                right-click on the selected photo and then click on the Perfectly Clear Image option.To
                remove the enhancement, do the same process.</p>
                <blockquote>
                    <p>
                        <a href="#designtop">
                            <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                border="0" />
                            Back to top</a></p>
                </blockquote>
            </li>
            <li><strong><a id="design10" name="design10"></a>How do I change my photos to a sepia
                or black and white colour tone?</strong><br />
                Right-click on the selected photo, select Filter and then click on your preference.
                Or you can also click on the B&amp;W Filter (insert icon) or Sepia Filter (insert
                icon) at the editing taskbar.</p>
                <blockquote>
                    <p>
                        <a href="#designtop">
                            <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                border="0" />
                            Back to top</a></p>
                </blockquote>
            </li>
            <li><strong><a id="design11" name="design11"></a>What does the Fade command do?</strong><br />
                The Fade command is best used if you wish to make a photo less prominent. By selecting
                a higher Fade percentage, the lesser prominent your selected photo will be. Its
                effect is almost as if a white tinge was overlaid on the photo.</p>
                <blockquote>
                    <p>
                        <a href="#designtop">
                            <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                border="0" />
                            Back to top</a></p>
                </blockquote>
            </li>
            <li><strong><a id="design12" name="design12"></a>I wish to add borders around my photos.
                How do I do it?</strong><br />
                Look for the Picture Borders option at the bottom panel where your photo thumbnails
                are displayed. A variety of borders will then be opened up for your selection. Select
                the border of your choice and then drag and drop the border thumbnail on to your
                photo.</p>
                <blockquote>
                    <p>
                        <a href="#designtop">
                            <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                border="0" />
                            Back to top</a></p>
                </blockquote>
            </li>
            <li><strong><a id="design13" name="design13"></a>How do I remove the borders then?</strong><br />
                Easy! Right-click on the respective photo &gt; Edit &gt; Remove Border.</p>
                <blockquote>
                    <p>
                        <a href="#designtop">
                            <img alt="^" src="http://photobookmart.co.in/images/arrowup.gif" width="11" height="10"
                                border="0" />
                            Back to top</a></p>
                </blockquote>
            </li>
            <li><strong><a id="design14" name="design14"></a>Can I add a shadow behind my photos?</strong><br />
                Not a problem! Just make sure you’ve selected the photo to have a shadow, then click
                on the Add Drop Shadow icon (insert icon). You can also find this command when you
